content.Info:
Background Node

Resizable background node to make navigation easier.

Double Click to change it's title.

Right Click - Set Color to change it's color.

Nodes dragged onto the background node will 'stick' to it, and will move with the background node when that is moved.

Info Node

resizable, with editable text

Combine Conditioning Node:

Used to combine Stable Diffusion conditionings,
for an example when using Set Conditioning Area node on a conditioning, you will have to combine it with an other one to composite the different areas.

Set Conditioning Area Node:

Takes a Stable Diffusion conditioning, ands set's it to be at a realite location in the latent space. 

By creating two conditionings, setting each to a different location in X or Y, you can combine them with a Combine Conditioning node, and feed the output to a sampler node to get a sample of both conditionings.

Apply ControlNet Node:

Regular controlnet's work by loading a ControlNet Model with a loader node, and by using an Image Operator to preprocess the input image for the chosen ControlNet with the operator of the same name.

"reference" type ControlNet does not need a ControlNet model, nor preprocessing the image, it just takes the reference image, and in this case, you can also ignore the conditioning output, as reference ControlNet is directly injected into the loaded Stable Diffusion model. In any other case, use the Conditioning output with the sampler node's input to get the effect.

DaraMerger Node:

DATA objects are always dictionaries, and sometimes you will want to merge them.

Execute Node:

Simple Execution Button

Useful for loops.
